  "@type": "Article",
  "dateModified": "2026-03-04",
  "datePublished": "2026-03-04",
  "description": "A hashtag is a word or phrase prefixed with the # symbol, used as a tag within social media and web platforms to mark content as relevant to a topic. The convention was proposed by Chris Messina on Twitter in August 2007 as a way to group conversations around shared topics without requiring any platform infrastructure beyond text search. Twitter initially had no formal tag system; Messina\u0026rsquo;s proposal succeeded because it was simple, required no platform support, and could be adopted unilaterally by any user.\n",
